description: Open the inspection panel of the control module and visually inspect the internal circuit while the system operates. Specifically, look for any indicator LED or component tied to the light‑sensor/comparator output or relay drive that might itself blink every ~20 seconds (for example, an internal status LED, test lamp, or other load that could momentarily steal current or disturb the circuit). Note whether any internal LED or device blinks off/on in exact synchrony with the main lamp’s half‑second turn‑off., outcome='The control module inspection panel was opened successfully, but the simulation indicates the circuit is in an unstable or oscillating state. All visually inspected components (ambient light sensor, control relay, sensitivity and timing potentiometers, and sensor bias resistor) show no observable internal faults, with the relay closed and the potentiometers at wiper positions 0.5 (sensitivity) and 1.0 (timing).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=55.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> ambient sensor module output vs load module lamp node,
description: With power ON, connect a voltmeter between the control module positive output terminal and the internal lamp node in the load module (junction between the series diode and the two lamps). Observe this differential voltage continuously for at least 30 seconds while the lamp operates. Report whether any momentary non‑zero voltage (more than a few tens of millivolts) appears between these two points in synchrony with the lamp’s brief turn‑off., outcome='During the 30-second observation, the control module positive output terminal remained at approximately 11.85 V, and the internal lamp node was at approximately 11.06 V relative to ground. This indicates a persistent differential voltage of about 0.8 V between these two points while the lamp was operating.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=45.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> ambient sensor module output vs. load module 0V return,
description: With power ON, measure the DC voltage between the control module’s positive output terminal and the load module’s negative/return terminal (i.e., directly across the entire load module including its internal diode and lamps). Observe this voltage continuously for at least 30 seconds while the lamp operates, and report whether it remains steady or shows any fluctuation in sync with the lamp’s previous blinking., outcome='The requested action could not be mapped to any recognized diagnostic operation. Only actions from the available action list are supported (e.g. measure_voltage, test_continuity, inspect_connections, verify_repair, …).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=0.0, cost_breakdown=[], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> load module total supply (between control + output and load − return),
description: With power ON, measure the DC voltage directly across the load module by placing the meter leads on the control module’s positive output terminal and the load module’s negative/return terminal. Observe continuously for at least 30 seconds. Report the approximate voltage and whether it remains steady or fluctuates in any way while the lamp operates., outcome='The measurement step did not execute successfully because no target with role "subject" was provided. No voltage readings or stability observations were obtained across the control module’s positive output terminal and the load module’s negative/return terminal.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=20.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> load module total supply between control + output and load − return,
description: With power ON, correctly configure the measurement to read the DC voltage directly across the load module: place the meter’s positive lead on the control module positive output terminal and the negative lead on the load module negative/return terminal (designate this node pair explicitly as the measurement subject). Observe this voltage continuously for at least 30 seconds while the lamp operates, and report its approximate value and whether it remains steady or shows any fluctuation in sync with the lamp’s previous blinking., outcome='The requested voltage measurement across the control module positive output and load module negative/return was not performed. The step failed because no target with role "subject" (the specified node pair for the measurement) was provided.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=20.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> load module total supply between control + output and load − return (node pair as explicit subject),
description: With power ON, measure the DC voltage directly across the load module by defining the node pair as the measurement subject: meter positive lead on the control module positive output terminal, meter negative lead on the load module negative/return terminal. Observe this voltage continuously for at least 30 seconds while the lamp operates, and report its approximate value and whether it remains steady or fluctuates in sync with the lamp’s previous blinking., outcome='Measured voltage at Control Output Cable (+) is approximately 11.85 V, and at Load Input Cable (−) is approximately 0.04 V (both with respect to ground). The simulator reports that the circuit did not converge and is in an unstable or oscillating state.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> system operating state after most recent (simulated) diagnostics,
description: Re‑check and explicitly state the *current* symptom: with the present settings of both potentiometers (timing at 1.0, sensitivity at 0.5) and all modules connected as verified, does the main lamp still blink off for about half a second every ~20 s, or is it now continuously on with no observable blinking? Carefully observe for at least 60 seconds and report the behavior., outcome='The requested action could not be mapped to any recognized diagnostic operation. Only actions from the available action list are supported (e.g. measure_voltage, test_continuity, inspect_connections, verify_repair, …).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=0.0, cost_breakdown=[], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> main lamp operating behavior,
description: With the system powered and both potentiometers at their current positions (timing 1.0, sensitivity 0.5), carefully observe the main lamp for at least 60 seconds and verify whether it still turns off briefly every ~20 seconds or now remains steadily on. Use the dedicated 'verify_repair' / symptom-check operation if available so the simulator accepts the observation., outcome='The main lamp has been marked as the hypothesis-verification target.  \nThe simulation did not converge and reports the circuit is in an unstable or oscillating state.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=120.0, cost_breakdown=[('verify_repair', 120.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
